  <steps>
    <step num="0">Preheat oil to about 160˚C (320˚F). </step>
    <step num="1">Season both sides of the chicken wings with salt and pepper. Coat with potato starch. </step>
    <step num="2">Fry the wings at 160˚C (320˚F) approximately 7 minutes. </step>
    <step num="3">Heat oil to about 180˚C (350˚F). Fry the wings until golden brown, about 3 minutes. Drain them on paper towels. Set aside. </step>
    <step num="4">Make the glaze. Combine all the glaze ingredients in a shallow pan and bring it to a simmer. Reduce until thick. Toss in the wings. </step>
    <step num="5">Sprinkle toasted white sesame. </step>
    <step num="6">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
